The paper deals with explaining machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of cooperative game theory to attribute predictions to input features falls under the category of computational economics (cs.CE) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the cognitive psychology concept of Norm Theory, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
